@startuml
title Raspberry Pi 5 Vehicle Signals Communication Workflow

actor "Driver" as Driver
participant "Joystick ECU\n(Arduino)" as JoystickECU
participant "Door RFID ECU\n(Arduino + RC522)" as RfidECU
participant "Mosquitto\n(MQTT Broker)" as Broker
participant "MQTT-to-gRPC Bridge" as Bridge
participant "Kuksa Databroker" as Kuksa
participant "Kuksa CAN Provider" as CAN
participant "Blinker ECU\n(MCU1 LED Control)" as MCU
participant "VSS Consumers\n(Fleet/UI/CLI)" as Consumers

== Command path (driver input to actuators) ==
Driver -> JoystickECU: Move joystick / press button
JoystickECU -> Broker: Publish JSON on InVehicleTopics
Broker -> Bridge: Deliver MQTT message
Bridge -> Kuksa: gRPC Val/Set (VSS updates)
Kuksa -> CAN: Target value subscription (val2dbc)
CAN -> MCU: CAN frame BlinkerCommand (ID 288)

== Driver identity path (RFID to VSS) ==
Driver -> RfidECU: Present RFID card
RfidECU -> Broker: Publish {"Vehicle.Driver.Identifier.Subject":"<UID>"}
Broker -> Bridge: Deliver MQTT message
Bridge -> Kuksa: Set Vehicle.Driver.Identifier.Subject (string)

== Feedback path (bus state back to VSS) ==
MCU -> CAN: CAN frame BlinkerStatus (ID 289)
CAN -> Kuksa: Write current values (dbc2val)
Kuksa -> Consumers: Read/Subscribe signal state

@enduml
